														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1841711">
									

<p>Not quite right. &quot;Uncontained&quot; means that its effects aren't contained, but we can still suppress information about it. &quot;Explained&quot;, by the example of 8900-EX, includes ones where we literally cannot prevent all of humanity from being exposed to it, so we accept it as normal. This is why Explained articles are so fundamentally difficult to write; it's such a narrow space that it's hard to write something with a degree of plausibility.</p>

							</div>

								
					
